{"TopicId":171627,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Normalize the Mousewheel","CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-03T22:33:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-03T22:33:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNormalize the mousewheel in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 In the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, mw scrolls up and down the ship, while in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, it zooms in and out.\u00A0 Shift-MW zooms in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, and moves up and down in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\u00A0 It\u0027d be nice if the same commands did the same function in both buildings.\u00A0\u00A0 Everytime I switch to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, I get all wonky trying to adjust the camera.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T01:13:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it\u0027s because of how(what?) these buildings are supposed to be used for. In \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E you build vertically, in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E horizontally. I know the controls are much different but I got used to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T01:19:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223309600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171627\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520126031\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it\u0027s because of how(what?) these buildings are supposed to be used for. In \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E you build vertically, in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E horizontally. I know the controls are much different but I got used to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat theory has merit, [ but the rest of the controls (WASD) doesn\u2019t align with the flight axis, but rather with the gravity vector, creating confusion. Either all of them go that way, or none of them; not some of them.]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT: DOH!\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003EThat\u0027s exactly what it does.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat explanation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-04T01:40:20Z\u0022 title=\u002203/04/2018 01:40  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 4, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbart\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T01:52:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223309600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171627\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520126031\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it\u0027s because of how(what?) these buildings are supposed to be used for. In \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E you build vertically, in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E horizontally. I know the controls are much different but I got used to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what I figured, but it\u0027s still very annoying.\u00A0 You get used to the controls doing A in one building, and they switch to B in the other.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the very least, an option to toggle this would be nice.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T14:09:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2562039962\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/121386-131-wasd-editor-camera-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use and highly recommend \u0022flying invisible\u00A0head\u0022 mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t even imagine going back to the wonky stock system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T15:36:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWASD editor for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T19:04:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll have to check that one out.\u00A0 Thanks guys\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}